Utilizing the detector’s capabilities to record the time-of-flight of the incident neutrons, the energy-dependent transmission spectra of the melamine, the water, and the ion exchange resin were analyzed. For this purpose, the temporal profiles of the transmissions were determined with the help of ImageJ’s Plot Z-axis Profile function for the respective regions-of-interest covered by these materials. This resulted in transmission over time-of-arrival in the detector’s clock time with a temporal bin width of 1.5625 ns corresponding to the LumaCam’s resolution (c.f. “Data analysis setup”). The time-of-arrival was converted to energy via the relativistic conversion formula:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
